<HL>
   Letters to the Editor:
   Services to Alleviate
   Burden of Alzheimer's
</HL>
<DATE>
05/31/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A15
</SO>
<IN>
HEALTH CARE PROVIDERS, MEDICINE, DENTISTRY (HEA)
</IN>
<LP>
   I want to express sincere appreciation for Brent Bower's
May 2 page-one article, "Slow Death: Life With Alzheimer's Is
Often the Hardest on Families of the Sick."
   It was an exceptionally fine job of presenting the
devastating effects of Alzheimer's disease and the enormous
emotional and financial burdens carried by the family members
who care for the patient at home.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   We would like your readers to know that the COPSA
Institute for Alzheimer's Disease and Related Disorders is
part of the Community Mental Health Center at Piscataway, a
health-care facility of the University of Medicine and
Dentistry of New Jersey. For information about Alzheimer's
disease and available services, people may call
1-800-424-2494 (New Jersey residents only) or 1-201-463-4430.
   B. Lee Joslin
   Director
   COPSA Institute for Alzheimer's Disease
   and Related Disorders
   University of Medicine and Dentistry of New Jersey
   Piscataway, N.J.
</TEXT>
