   Business Brief -- Central Bancorp.:
   Board Rejects Takeover Bid,
   Sets Stock Buy-Back Instead
</HL>
<DATE>
05/31/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B10
</SO>
<CO>
   CBWA
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
</IN>
<LP>
   Central Bancorp., Wenatchee, Wash., said its board
rejected an unsolicited cash offer of $12.30 a share from
another financial institution and will go ahead instead with
a repurchase stock plan. A company spokesman declined to name
the rejected bidder.
   Central Bancorp., the parent company of Central Washington
Bank with $105 million in assets, said it will purchase up to
150,000 shares of company stock at $10 a share. The plan was
recently approved by federal bank regulatory authorities.
Central Bancorp. expects to start purchasing the shares
within a few weeks.
</LP>
