<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   ShowBiz Pizza Time Inc., Irving, Texas, said its board
approved a change in its 1.3 million warrants outstanding,
allowing holders to exercise them between Aug. 15, 1990, and
May 2, 1993. Previously, the pizza restaurant chain said,
holders could exercise the warrants only in the 90 days
preceding May 2, 1993.
   The warrants, which are exercisable at $4 a share, were
issued when ShowBiz was spun off from Integra-A Hotel &amp;
